        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 23 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Bernice, or 15 miles east of Homer, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bernice, Cooley, Dubach, Lisbon, Lillie, Corinth and Shiloh.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
